# Model Rules - Unusualify Modularity

## Base Structure

```php
namespace Modules\{ModuleName}\Entities;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Unusualify\Modularity\Entities\Traits\HasMedias;
use Unusualify\Modularity\Entities\Traits\IsTranslatable;

class {ModelName} extends Model
{
    use SoftDeletes, HasMedias, IsTranslatable;

    protected $table = 'table_name';

    protected $fillable = [];

    protected $casts = [];

    public $timestamps = true;

    // Modularity-specific properties
    public $checkboxes = [];
    public $nullable = [];
    public $translatedAttributes = [];
}
```

## Essential Properties

### Fillable & Guarded

```php
// Explicit fillable (recommended)
protected $fillable = [
    'name',
    'email',
    'status',
    'metadata',
];

// Or use guarded (less safe)
protected $guarded = ['id'];

// Mass assignment protection off (not recommended)
protected $guarded = [];
```

### Casts (Type Conversion)

```php
protected $casts = [
    // Boolean
    'is_active' => 'boolean',
    'published' => 'boolean',

    // Integer
    'views_count' => 'integer',
    'priority' => 'integer',

    // Float/Decimal
    'price' => 'decimal:2',
    'rating' => 'float',

    // DateTime
    'published_at' => 'datetime',
    'expires_at' => 'datetime:Y-m-d H:i:s',

    // Date
    'birth_date' => 'date',

    // JSON (arrays/objects)
    'settings' => 'array',
    'metadata' => 'object',
    'tags' => 'collection',

    // Encrypted
    'secret' => 'encrypted',
    'api_key' => 'encrypted:array',
];
```

### Modularity-Specific Properties

```php
// Fields that should default to false if not present
public $checkboxes = [
    'is_featured',
    'is_public',
    'send_notifications',
];

// Fields that should default to null if not present
public $nullable = [
    'deleted_by',
    'approved_at',
    'notes',
];

// Translatable attributes (requires IsTranslatable trait)
public $translatedAttributes = [
    'title',
    'description',
    'content',
];
```

## Relationships

### Basic Relationships

- Use \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\* on return type of relationships

```php
// One to One
public function profile(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasOne
{
    return $this->hasOne(Profile::class);
}

public function user(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\BelongsTo
{
    return $this->belongsTo(User::class);
}

// One to Many
public function posts(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasMany
{
    return $this->hasMany(Post::class);
}

public function category(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\BelongsTo
{
    return $this->belongsTo(Category::class);
}

// Many to Many
public function tags(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\BelongsToMany
{
    return $this->belongsToMany(Tag::class)
        ->withTimestamps()
        ->withPivot('order', 'metadata');
}

// Has Many Through
public function comments(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasManyThrough
{
    return $this->hasManyThrough(
        Comment::class,
        Post::class,
        'author_id',    // Foreign key on posts
        'post_id',      // Foreign key on comments
        'id',           // Local key on users
        'id'            // Local key on posts
    );
}

// Has One Through
public function latestPost(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\HasOneThrough
{
    return $this->hasOneThrough(Post::class, Author::class)
        ->latest();
}
```

### Polymorphic Relationships

```php
// Polymorphic One to Many
public function comments(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\MorphMany
{
    return $this->morphMany(Comment::class, 'commentable');
}

public function commentable(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\MorphTo
{
    return $this->morphTo();
}

// Polymorphic Many to Many
public function tags(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\MorphToMany
{
    return $this->morphToMany(Tag::class, 'taggable');
}

// Inverse
public function posts(): \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\MorphedByMany
{
    return $this->morphedByMany(Post::class, 'taggable');
}
```

